Koi herpesvirus disease, Canada
-------------------------------
Information received on 7 Sep 2018 from Dr Jaspinder Komal, Deputy Chief Veterinary Officer, Canadian Food Inspection Agency, Canadian Food Inspection Agency, Ottawa, Canada

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 16 Jul 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 27 Aug 2018
Report dare: 7 Sep 2018
Date event resolved: 28 Aug 2018
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Koi herpesvirus [KHV]
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Cypress county, Alberta
Date of start of the outbreak: 16 Jul 2018
Outbreak status: resolved on 28 Aug 2018
Epidemiological unit: pond
Water type: fresh water
Population type: farmed
Production system: closed
Affected animals:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Koi Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / 100 percent / 81 percent / 75 / 75 / 61 / 14 / 0
Affected population: Ornamental backyard pond (pets)

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages], expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Koi Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / 100 / 81.33 / 81.33 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: introduction of new live animals

Control measures
Measures applied: traceability; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Fisheries water institute (national laboratory) / Koi carp (_Cyprinus carpio_ (koi)) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 16 Jul 2018 / Positive
Fisheries water institute (National laboratory) / Koi carp (_Cyprinus carpio_ (koi)) / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 16 Jul 2018 / Positive
Fisheries water institute (National laboratory) / Koi carp (_Cyprinus carpio_ (koi)) / gene sequencing / 26 Aug 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

